# Infinite OS — environment configuration
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in what you need. NOTHING here is required to *try*
# Infinite: `infinite setup` provisions the local stack and writes most config
# (DB URL, encryption key, model auth) into `.growth-os/` for you. This file is
# for running `docker compose` directly or for bring-your-own keys/overrides.
#
# NEVER commit `.env` (it is gitignored). Use placeholders only in this template.

# =============================================================================
# LOCAL DOCKER STACK (docker-compose.yml)
# =============================================================================
# The `infinite` CLI auto-sources these from `.growth-os/.env` (it derives
# POSTGRES_USER/PASSWORD/DB from that file's DATABASE_URL). You only need a
# repo-root `.env` here if you run `docker compose` DIRECTLY.

# Postgres password — baked into the postgres volume on FIRST init. Do NOT change
# it later for an existing volume (you would lose access to synced data).
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=

# The container DATABASE_URL is derived from POSTGRES_USER/PASSWORD/DB at host
# `postgres`; you do NOT need to set it for compose. The host CLI uses its own
# localhost URL.
# DATABASE_URL=

# Code identity for app/worker. `infinite start` sets this to the git HEAD so
# `docker compose up -d` recreates the containers when the code moved. Defaults
# to "dev". Only relevant if you run `docker compose` directly:
#   export GROWTH_OS_CODE_VERSION="$(git rev-parse HEAD)"
# GROWTH_OS_CODE_VERSION=

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY / AUTH
# =============================================================================
# 32+ byte secret that encrypts stored connection credentials.
#   Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# LOAD-BEARING: rotating this orphans existing connections (every source must
# re-authenticate). The old `dev-change-me-*` default is blocked.
# GROWTH_OS_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# Install auth tokens for the local API (operator = read+write, read = read-only).
#   Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# GROWTH_OS_OPERATOR_TOKEN=
# GROWTH_OS_READ_TOKEN=

# =============================================================================
# MODEL PROVIDER (bring your own — optional)
# =============================================================================
# `infinite setup` can import a local Codex or Claude login automatically. Set a
# key here only to bring your own provider credentials explicitly.
#
# OpenAI / Codex (used for the codex model provider when not importing a login):
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
#
# Anthropic / Claude (API-key auth; Claude-via-OAuth is not supported):
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# GOOGLE ANALYTICS 4 — bring-your-own OAuth client (optional, advanced)
# =============================================================================
# By default GA4 connects via the bundled quick-connect client. To use your own
# Google Cloud OAuth client instead (BYO), point at a downloaded client JSON, or
# set the id/secret directly. See the GA4 setup docs.
# GROWTH_OS_GA4_OAUTH_CLIENT_FILE=/path/to/oauth-client.json
# GROWTH_OS_GA4_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
# GROWTH_OS_GA4_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
# GROWTH_OS_GA4_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=
